WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:04,950
If skeptics work is growing and adoption is not, the breakdown is usually in live decisions.

00:05,000 --> 00:09,950
Without a clear review habit, superstars quality drifts even when effort increases. Measurement becomes useful when...

00:10,000 --> 00:14,950
Pick one owner and one metric, then run one weekly checkpoint in the workstream.

00:15,000 --> 00:19,950
Prototype quickly, test in live work for one week, and log evidence before scaling.

00:20,000 --> 00:24,950
This usually improves first-pass quality, cleaner superstars handoffs, and faster team adoption.

00:25,000 --> 00:29,950
Which weekly checkpoint would improve decision quality first?
